The grid that has the highest percentage of wind is germany at
4.5%, that is not baseload, it is not even peaking, it is a miniscule
percentage that is fully covered by the balance of the grid, when I am
speaking of baseload, I am speaking of the 50-75% of power that is
running all the time, and wind is really no good for that.  I am not
saying it is not useful, I am saying that it is limited to 20% before
the installed price needs to increase to take into account for the
storage or long distance transmission, as such it is not and will not
in the forseeable future be an acceptable option for primary baseload.
